column1: # SOURCE: Computed from weather data using simplified PV model
# DESCRIPTION: Normalized daily PV power output per kW of installed capacity for three agri-PV density variants (low/medium/high ground coverage)

# LOGIC: PV output = solar_irradiance * tilt_factor(1.05) * temp_factor * (1-system_losses). Temp factor uses cell temp model: T_cell = T_avg + 25C + density_adjustment. Temperature coefficient = -0.4%/C from 25C reference. System losses = 15%.
# ASSUMPTIONS: Fixed-tilt 28deg south-facing panels. Module efficiency ~19%. High density panels run 2C cooler (shading effect)
column2: low density run 2C hotter. All panels receive full irradiance (panels above crops
column3: not shaded by each other). Tilt factor approximate; full pvlib model would be more accurate.
